Free State police say the teenager&#8217;s classmate brought the bullet to school on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG It has emerged that a heavy calibre bullet has exploded in a school boy s hand, causing extensive damage.Free State police say the teenager s classmate brought the bullet to school on Tuesday.While playing during break time, one of the boys hit the bullet with an iron causing it to explode.Spokesperson Kethabile Mofokeng says a case has been opened under the Firearms Protection Act. He showed the bullet to his four friends and one of his friend who is a 13-year-old grabbed it from him hit several times on an iron, which led to the explosion. The 13-year-old sustained injuries on his fingers. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)